4 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 1804, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 1804. A. During any period of supervision, the
7 Commissioner may appoint a supervisor for such insurer and provide
8 that the insurer may not do any of the following things without the
9 prior approval of the Commissioner or his the supervisor:
10 1. Dispose, convey or encumber any of its assets or its
11 business in force;
12 2. Withdraw funds from bank accounts;
13 3. Lend funds;
14 4. Invest funds;
15 5. Transfer property;
16 6. Incur any debt, obligation or liability;
17 7. Merge or consolidate with another company; or
18 8. Enter into any new reinsurance contract or treaty.
19 B. In addition, the Commissioner or the supervisor may require
20 of the insurer, the following:
21 1. Periodic actuarial reviews; and
22 2. That the insurer limit or cease writing certain lines of
23 insurance.
24
SB1916 HFLR Page 8
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 C. Within the limits of duties imposed upon them, appointed
2 supervisors shall possess all the powers given to a supervisor and,
3 in the exercise of those powers, shall be subject to all duties,
4 powers, and limitations imposed upon the supervisor.
