12 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1813 of Title 36, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 The Insurance Commissioner, his or her employees, current or
16 former appointed supervisor or conservator, or the supervisor’s or
17 conservator’s contractors shall:
18 1. Have no liability and no cause of action of any nature shall
19 arise against such person for any action taken in performance of his
20 or her powers and duties pursuant to this act; and
21 2. Be indemnified to the same extent as a receiver and the
22 receiver’s employees and contractors are indemnified pursuant to
23 Section 1937 of Title 36 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
