3 SECTION 8. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1914.1 of Title 36, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. The Oklahoma Receivership Office shall be authorized to
7 deposit funds and assets held prior to the effective date of this
8 act pursuant to Sections 1901 through 1938 of Title 36 of the
9 Oklahoma Statutes into one or more accounts or investment accounts,
10 in one or more state or national banks, saving banks, savings and
11 loan associations, trust companies, investment firms, or other
12 appropriate financial institutions. Funds deposited pursuant to
13 this section may be:
14 1. Combined to yield the highest rate of return on deposits, or
15 in any other way to facilitate the efficient operation of the
16 Oklahoma Receivership Office and the respective receiverships under
17 its jurisdiction; and
18 2. Used for the purpose of operating the division, for the
19 expenses of the respective jurisdiction in accordance with the
20 provisions of Sections 1901 through 1938 of Title 36 of the Oklahoma
21 Statutes.
22 B. Funds deposited pursuant to subsection A of this section
23 shall be continuing funds, are not funds of this state, the
